    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing copy_uci_indication_PUSCH implementation causing UCI PUSCH data loss\n\n### Summary\nThe `copy_uci_indication_PUSCH()` function was referenced in VNF code but the actual implementation was missing from the codebase. This caused UCI indication data for PUSCH PDU types to be improperly handled, with log messages showing \"unhandled NFAPI_NR_UCI_PUSCH_PDU_TYPE\". \n\nThe root cause was that while the function was called, there was no proper implementation to copy the dynamically allocated payload data in UCI PUSCH structures.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/inc/nr_fapi_p7_utils.h`: New header file with function declarations for UCI indication copying\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: New implementation file with proper memory handling for UCI PUSCH data\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/CMakeLists.txt`: Added new source file to build\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/Makefile.am`: Added build configuration for new fapi library\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/Makefile.am`: Added fapi directory to build\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running OAI gNB with UCI indications containing PUSCH PDU types, the VNF logs will show:\n```\n[ERROR] unhandled NFAPI_NR_UCI_PUSCH_PDU_TYPE\n```\n\nThis occurs because the shallow copy in the VNF code (`uci_ind->uci_list[i] = ind->uci_list[i];`) doesn't properly copy dynamically allocated payload data, leading to data loss or corruption when the source data is freed.\n\nThe new implementation properly allocates and copies all payload data, ensuring UCI PUSCH indications are handled correctly.\n"
}